# [HRPC](../wg/hrpc.html)

## Summary

The Human Rights Protocol Considerations (HRPC) research group met for a one-hour session. The meeting focused on the intersection of human rights, internet architecture, and standardization processes. 

The session featured two primary presentations: 
1. An analysis of the organizational and technical impacts of migrating public interest internet governance infrastructure to commercial hyperscaler clouds ("CloudRift").
2. An update from the Office of the United Nations High Commissioner for Human Rights (OHCHR) on integrating human rights due diligence and checklists into technical standards bodies.

## Key Discussion Points

